NAME
lxcu-copy -- Start a linux container.
SYNOPSIS
lxcu-copy {-h|-V}
lxcu-copy -n SOURCE_CONTAINER -N DESTINATION_CONTAINER
lxcu-copy [OPTIONS]
DESCRIPTION
This script copies an existing linux container to a new one. The only extra task
performed compared to lxc-copy is that the script also copies any extra lxcu
config files, (such as for bridges).
OPTIONS
-h, --help Display this help information

-n, --from-name 'container name'

-N, --to-name 'container name'

-V, --version Print script version information
EXIT STATUS
0 - Success

1 - General failure

64 - Error in command line
FILES
lxcu.conf  The script reads the configuration file to set default values.
